of the Dallas Business Council for the Arts Leadership Arts Institute. From 2008-2013 Megan was a clarinetist in the Navy Music Program and was stationed in Virginia, Hawaii and Louisiana. She performed in the woodwind quintet, wind symphony and ceremonial band and was a recipient of the Pacific Fleet Command Sailor of the Quarter. Megan is a member of Sigma Alpha Iota, an international fraternity for women, and was the 2008 National Collegiate Leadership Award Winner. Megan is a native of Oak Ridge, New Jersey, and received a BM in Music Education and a BA in Education from Rowan University as well as a BS in Organizational Leadership from Thomas Edison State College. She is currently pursuing an MA in Arts Administration and an MBA from Southern Methodist University in Dallas, TX. Visit Us Music Building 415 Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 Mail Us University of North Texas 1155 Union Circle #311367 Denton, TX 76203-5017 Contact Us 940-565-2791 music.information@unt.edu Technical issues? Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 09, 2017 | Important Links 